# 4) Borders, dashed, border-left, border styles

```css
/* border shorthand: width style color */
div {
  border: 2px solid #000;
}

/* left border only */
img {
  border-left: 4px dashed orange;
}

/* border shorthand broken out */
border-width: 4px;
border-style: dashed; /* solid, dashed, dotted, double, groove, ridge, inset, outset, none */
border-color: orange;

/* rounded corners */
border-radius: 8px;
```

* If the user wrote "putos cuadraditos" — likely they meant dotted/dashed small squares — use `dotted` or `dashed`. `dotted` draws dots; `dashed` draws short lines; `double` makes two parallel lines.
* Border can be per-side: `border-top`, `border-right`, `border-bottom`, `border-left`.

