# 7) `display:block`, `text-align`, centering text & images

* `display: block;` forces the element to behave like a block-level element (takes full width unless width set).
* `text-align: right;` (applies to inline content inside a block) — aligns inline children (text, inline elements).

```css
#img {
  text-align: right;  /* this affects inline content inside the element with id="img" */
}

/* to right-align an image using its container */
figure { text-align: right; }
figure img { display: inline-block; }
```

To center a block element horizontally:

```css
.element { width: 500px; margin: 0 auto; } /* left+right margins auto center it */
```

