# 8) Media queries (responsive rules)

You gave an example — explained:

```css
@media all and (max-width: 500px) {
  img {
    border: orange dashed;
    width: 300px;
  }
}
```

**Meaning**: When the viewport (or device) width is 500px or less, apply these rules. `all` means every media type. `max-width` is the most common for mobile-first or responsive tweaks.

**Mobile-first recommendation**: write base styles for small screens, then use `@media (min-width: ...)` to expand for larger screens.

