# 12) Accessibility & best practices (short & sharp)

* Always provide `alt` attributes for `<img>`.
* Use semantic tags instead of lots of `<div>` where possible.
* Prefer `button` elements for clickable UI instead of clickable `<div>`.
* Ensure sufficient color contrast for readability.
* Use `aria-` attributes only when necessary — semantic HTML often avoids them.

---

# 13) Common exam pitfalls & what they test

* Confusing `display: inline` vs `inline-block` (inline ignores width/height).
* `%` in `margin-left: x%` relative to containing block width, not element width.
* `text-align` affects inline content inside a block, not the block itself.
* `border: dashed` vs `border-style: dotted` — visual difference.
* Specificity mistakes (IDs beat classes).
* Box-model: forgetting `box-sizing: border-box` leads to unexpected sizes.
* Media queries orientation: `min-width` vs `max-width`.

